Description: WE ARE FLORIDA'S OLDEST VINTAGE GUITAR SHOP ! 1966 Fender Telecaster as played by "Rolling Stone" Mick Taylor w/his Band in Miami ! Beautiful original See-thru Blonde finished Ash body, it sports a fabulous Maple Cap neck dated September 1966 that has clear overspray on its fingerboard & back side yet its headstock is original finish w/its original Transitional Telecaster decal still in place, she still has her original Kluson double line tuners, it has 2 cloth covered wire original pickups w/a set of original '66 pots, its got a cool Black Bakelite Reissue pickgard in place for that 1952 vibe, its input jack now wears a LP type jack plate, a modern adjustable bridge & reissue dome knobs, this is a fantastic sounding & playing Tele that was used by Rolling Stone “Mick Taylor” when in Miami playing a live gig w/his then band called “Tumblin Dice“ w/bandmates Bobby Keyes, Lester Chambers, Nicky Hopkins & Fuzzy Samuels, it is documented w/a photo from the gig c.1990, she’s a great vintage axe w/some monster history easily made a stock original again if desired, excellent overall & comes w/a nice hard case.
